    "body": "### Problem\n\nI've noticed that my Neovim sometimes hanged when I tried to exit for the past few days, forcing me to SIGKILL it.\n\nI've bisected the issue and got to this PR (https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/30872) (commit: 8c2d45be77299d6eb70165697bc5c29898cdb25e).\n\nI've managed to find a sure way to reproduce it using [Molten-nvim](https://github.com/benlubas/molten-nvim), but failed to make it work with a minimal example because of a call to `:UpdateRemotePlugin` that doesn't work for some reason (`E482: Can't open file /path/to/manifest for writing: no such file or directory`).\n\nThank you üôè \n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n- `minimal.lua`\n\n```lua\n-- Run this file as `nvim --clean -u ./minimal.lua file.py\n\nfor name, url in pairs {\n  molten = 'https://github.com/benlubas/molten-nvim',\n} do\n  local install_path = vim.fn.fnamemodify('nvim_issue/' .. name, ':p')\n  if vim.fn.isdirectory(install_path) == 0 then\n    vim.fn.system { 'git', 'clone', '--depth=1', url, install_path }\n  end\n  vim.opt.runtimepath:append(install_path)\nend\n\n-- ADD INIT.LUA SETTINGS _NECESSARY_ FOR REPRODUCING THE ISSUE\nvim.keymap.set('n', '<space>m', ':MoltenEvaluateLine<cr>')\n```\n\n- `file.py`\n```python\n# Do <leader>m on this file\nprint('hello world')\n\n# Then on this line\nimport duckdb\n```\n\n- `mkdir -p $HOME/.local/share/jupyter/runtime`\n- `nvim --clean -u minimal.lua file.py`\n- Find a way to make `:UpdateRemotePlugin` work.\n- You might need `pynvim` and `jupyter_client` installed in a venv first.\n- Then do `<space>m` on the first non commentated line. Then same on the second.\n- `:q`\n- It should hang.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nNo hanging.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.11.0-dev-1045+gb922b7d6d7\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno, not tested\n\n### Operating system/version\n\n6.11.5-zen1-1-zen\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nKitty master\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-kitty\n\n### Installation\n\nAUR package, with the git repository updated to the right commit with `makepkg -efsi` in between",
